@node "Einfuehrung" "Introduction"
 1. @{u}Introduction@{uu}

 GeoWorld was developed to set new standards in the relatively thinly
covered market of geography programs for the Amiga. Outstanding quality
to a favourable price (a good price-performance relationship) was, and
continues to be, our aim for software development. To my knowledge, there
are no other programs which match GeoWorld in terms of functionality or
have as good a price-performance relationship.

 Through exemplary support and future updates we would like to provide
GeoWorld as our contribution to the revival of the Amiga market...
@endnode


@node "Entwicklungsgeshichte" "Program Development"
 2. @{u}Program Development@{uu}

 Development on GeoWorld began in spring 1996 by the Beer Production team.

 It was created on an Amiga 1200 with Blizzard 1230/IV (68030 with
50 MHz) and 16 MB Fast-Ram, 340 MB hard disk and CDRom -
drive. Furthermore a good old Amiga 500 with 1 MB Ram assisted.

 On the software side, the main work was done in BlitzBasic v2.1 (with
expansions) as well as DeluxePaint v4.5, PersonalPaint v6.0, ImageFX v1.5,
the AZ-editor, DirOpus v4.11, Wordworth v5.0 and DataManager v1.0 (an
internal production for recording the GeoWorld data).

 The present version of GeoWorld began in 1991 with the first (unsuccessful)
attempts with AmigaBasic. A phase began in 1992 which saw GeoWorld coded in
AMOS-Basic, which, however, failed due to the diverse restraints of that
programming language. The project slept until the end of 1995, when I tried
again with AmigaE, which also was not crowned with success. Since spring /
summer in 1996 I have been programming GeoWorld in BlitzBasic v2.1, with my
brother Ronny caring for the graphics and (in part) the data. The first public
release (version 1.0) became available in December 1997...

 You can read about all the improvements since v1.0 in the @{"history" link "History"}.
@endnode

