@node "System" "System requirements"
 4. @{u}System requirements@{uu}

GeoWorld has the following requirements:

 Amiga with Kickstart/OS 2.0+
 AGA-chipset or Gfx-card
 3 MByte Ram (of that 1,5 MByte ChipRam is required)
 Reqtools-Library

 The commodity CycleToMenu 2.0 is also supported.
(© 1993-94 by Federico Giannici).
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
 5. @{u}Installation@{uu}

 GeoWorld is delivered with the standard installation program from
Commodore/Escom and can be installed with this easily, on to hard disk,
simply by double-clicking on the install icon for your language, and
following the instructions. An installation is necessary as there is
over 5MBytes of graphics and data - running from floppy disk is not
possible.

 In addition to the real program package still two types can be
installed, which we use even at running of GeoWorld.

The Installer is copyright 1990-95 by Commodore - Amiga, Inc.
respectively Escom.
@endnode

@node "Ueberblick" "Initial overview"
 6. @{u}Initial overview@{uu}

 GeoWorld has at its disposal an extensive data library, which
currently contains information about 192 independent countries and
the most important (politically) dependent countries. Altogether, this
version deals with 220 countries.

 However, this is not everything: GeoWorld also contains information
about more than 2000 German cities, as well as about the most important
international cities. At this time, data is contained for more than 4800
cities.

 All of this information can be printed out or stored for further work,
e.g. for use in your word processing.

 If you do not know how something works, pressing the "Help" key will make
GeoWorld show a help window with explanations about the gadgets and data
fields in the active window when the "Help" key was pressed.

 The knowledge you acquire with GeoWorld can be examined, and rated
with a quiz.

 Here once more is a summary of the most important features:

° Extensive data and graphics for the countries of the world (statistical data,
  economy, history etc., maps, flags and much more)
° Maps of the world, continents and individual countries on full screen (approx.
  5 Mbyte graphics)
° Ability to choose a country on the map of the world, or on the continental
  maps
° Data for all the major cities in the world as well as for the most important
  in Germany (drawn in the correct geographical position on the maps)
° Extensive search and sort functions
° Printing functions
° On-line help
° Quiz with highscore
° Adjustable Screenmode and font among others
° Ready to be translated to other languages


The maps window
---------------

 All graphic information, in GeoWorld, is shown in the map window,
except the flags.

 The first screen of GeoWorld always shows the map of the world. By
clicking on the map, you can zoom in to either the selected country or
continent, depending upon the setting in the control window.

 To read more about the "control centre" of GeoWorld look at @{"control window" link "Kontrollfenster" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Kontrollfenster" "Control window"
 7. @{u}Control window@{uu}

Country selection - brings up a selection window with all available countries;
                    if you have entered anything in the "Name" string gadget
                    then that name of country will be searched for (see below).

City selection    - like "Country selection", but works with cities

Search term       - Using this string gadget, it is possible to enter a search
"Name"              term for the country and city selections. The entered
                    search term will be used when the country or city selection
                    buttons are next pressed.

                    The search term refers exclusively to the name of the
                    country or city. For more extensive search functions, see
                    the @{"Maxi-Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0} section.

                    Possible search terms:
                    Complete name -> GeoWorld will try to find the country or
                                     city with this name. If it is found, then
                                     the information window will be displayed,
                                     for that country or city.

                    xxx*          -> The selection window will be shown, with
                                     all the countries or cities which start
                                     with the string "xxx".

                    *yyy          -> The selection window will be shown, with
                                     all the countries or cities which end
                                     with the string "yyy".

                    *zzz*         -> The selection window will be shown, with
                                     all the countries or cities which contain
                                     the string "zzz".

                     All strings entered into the "Name" search term are
                    treated as case insensitive.
                     If you enter a string and GeoWorld can not find any
                    matches, then a requester will tell you this, and the
                    selection window will not be shown. If GeoWorld only finds
                    one match while searching, then the information window for
                    this match will be shown, skipping the selection window.

Maxi - Search     - Offers the possibility to search using all the available
                    information on countries and cities, not only the name. It
                    is possible to search on multiple fields simultaneously. For
                    more information, see @{"Maxi - Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0}.

Movement buttons  - These four buttons move the currently displayed map in the
(L, R, U, D)        direction indicated by the button. If the map is already
                    showing the full width or height, then the L and R or U and
                    D buttons are disabled, respectively. The cursor keys also
                    perform these functions.

World map         - If the currently displayed map is either a continent or a
                    country, then this button will be enabled, and pressing it
                    allows you to return to the full world map.

Country info      - If the map window is displaying only a country, pressing
                    this button will bring up the information window for this
                    country.

Selection buttons - Determines where GeoWorld will zoom to when the world map
                    is clicked on. Options are:

                    O Continents    -> zoom to corresponding continent
                    O Countries     -> zoom to the chosen country
@endnode

@node "MaxiSuche" "Maxi-Search function"
 8. @{u}Maxi-Search function@{uu}

 The Maxi-Search function allows the user to search using all the available
information about countries and cities, and allows multiple simultaneous
search terms. Matches are shown in the selection window.

Not               - Ticking this box will make GeoWorld search for items which
                    match the opposite of what you have entered as search terms.

Country selection - This cycle gadget chooses whether to use the information
City selection      for the countries or cities while searching. The search
                    fields are labelled accordingly. The spacebar also changes
                    this option.

Start search      - Starts the search function. Results appear in the selection
                    window with the matching items, or a requester stating that
                    no matches were found.

Erase all         - Clears all entered search terms.


 The search terms can be numerical or alphabetical, depending upon what the
field is. There are two different types of entry possible:

Alphabetical fields: a name or any other word should be entered.

  Possible term types:
    complete word -> Items that match have exactly this string in the
                     appropriate data field.

    xxx*          -> Items match if the appropriate field starts with the
                     string "xxx".

    *yyy          -> Items match if the appropriate field ends with the
                     string "yyy".

    *zzz*         -> Items match if the appropriate field contains the
                     string "zzz".

  The alphabetical search fields are:
      Name, capital, languages, religions, currency, holidays, registration
      number (for countries)

      Name, country, federal state, circle, zip code (for cities)


Numerical fields: a number should be entered.

  Possible term types:
    1234  -> For an item to match, it must contain this value exactly.

    <1234 -> Items with a value less than "1234" will cause a match.

    >1234 -> Items with a value greater than "1234" will cause a match.

  The numerical search fields are:
    Area, inhabitants, population density, GNP (for countries)

    Inhabitants, year founded, altitude (for cities)
@endnode

@node "Laenderfenster" "Country information window"
 9. @{u}Country information window@{uu}

 It is from the country information window that all the data about a country
can be retrieved, from the vast amount of information that GeoWorld is able
to access. The country information window also allows you to view maps of
the country, or to bring up information for places that are connected to the
country (cities information, dependancies, etc.).

@{u}Items in window@{uu}

Title bar    - Short name of the country
Name         - Long name of the country (for example Republic,
               Kingdom and so on)
Dependent on - If the country depends on an other country you will
               get the name of the other country here. Using the "<<" button
               you can call up the country information window for that country
Area         - Area of the country in square kilometres
Inhabitants  - Number of inhabitants of the country
Population   - The average number of inhabitants per square kilometre
density
Capital      - Name of the capital city of this country
               (Pressing the ">>" button will bring up the city information
               window for the capital)
Languages    - Languages spoken in this country - starting with most frequently
               spoken language (official language)
Religions    - Religions practised in this country - starting with the most
               frequently practised
GNP          - Whole gross national product of the country and also the GNP
               per inhabitant
Currency     - Currency of the country - full name and abbreviation
               for example: 1 Dollar ($) = 100 Cents (C)
Holiday      - National holiday(s) of the country
Car          - International valid car registration of the country
registration


@{u}Buttons@{uu}

Cyclegadget  - Shows what information is currently being displayed in the
               country information window. When the window is first opened
               this always gets set to "General" (the fields described above
               are for the General option). Other available information sets
               are:
                   International Organisations that country is a member of
                   Politics - form of government
                   Nature and climate
                   Population
                   Economy
                   History
                   Others (time compared to CET - Central European Time)

               @{b}NEW:@{ub} You can also get information on the International
               Organisations that the country is a member of. Clicking on the
               name of an organisation will display the following information
               (about that organisation):
                   Abbreviated name
                   International name
                   German designation
                   Seat
                   Year founded
                   Members
               The other members of this organisation can be displayed in a
               country selection window, by selecting the Members item in the
               Project menu.

"<<" and ">>"  - Display what country this one depends on (if any) and display
                 the capital city, repectively.
City selection - Shows a selection window with all the citites of this
                 country, for which more information is available
Continent      - Draws the country in dark blue color on the correct
                 continental map
World map      - Draws the country in dark blue color on the world map
Show country   - If available, a detailed map of the country is displayed, and
                 if the "Larger cities show immediately" item is selected in
                 the preferences window, then the major cities in this country
                 will also be drawn.


@{u}Menu functions@{uu}

Project
  Dependencies - A selection window is displayed which contains all countries
                 or territories that belong (politically) to, and are dependent
                 on, the currently selected country.
  Close        - Closes the country information window


Country data
  General            - Choosing one of these menu items performs the same
  Organisations        function as setting the cycle gadget to the relevant
  Politics             item, and thus retrieving more information about the
  Nature               country
  Population
  Economy
  History
  Others


Others
  Print function - This menu item calls up the print function window, which
                   allows the information in the window to be printed, or all
                   the information about the current country.
                   Usage information can be found at @{"Print function" link "Druckausgabe" 0}.
@endnode

@node "StaedteFenster" "City information window"
 10. @{u}City information window@{uu}

 From the city information window, all available information about a city can
be retrieved. It is also possible to bring up the corresponding maps and
country information window.


@{u}Items in window@{uu}

Name         - Name of city. If the German name of the city is different from
               the domestic version, then the city name in the national language
               also appears here.
Country      - The country in which the selected city lies
State        - Shows the membership of the city to a state or similar (naming
               convention differs from country to country). This is normally the
               biggest regional structure in the country.
District     - Shows the membership of the city to a district or similar: this
               is normally the second biggest regional structure in a country.
               If necessary, this also shows that a city is either the capital
               of a country or independent.
Inhabitants  - The number of people living in the city. Suburbs of metropolises
               are not included in this value, but are included separately with
               their own information.
Year founded - The year in which the town was founded. If this is not exactly
               known, the year of award of the city charters and/or market
               rights or the year of the first authentic mention is shown.
Altitude     - Height of the town above the sea level (negative values mean a
               height underneath the sea level)
               For cities with large areas, the average height is used (between
               highest and lowest point within the city limits).
Post code    - Post code of the city (currently only for German, Austrian and
               Swiss cities).


@{u}Buttons@{uu}

Cyclegadget - Shows what information is currently being displayed about the
              selected city. When the City information window is first opened,
              the information on display will be "General", which is described
              above. Other available options are:
                Economy
                Infrastructure
                Tourism
                History
                Others

>>          - Pressing this button will bring up the country information
              window of the city's country.
Show city   - Pressing this button will load the map of the country (if
              available) and the city will be drawn at its correct geographical
              location. The symbol represents the size of the city.


@{u}Menu functions@{uu}

Project
  Show city - Selecting this item will load the map of the country (if
              available) and the city will be drawn at its correct geographical
              location. The symbol represents the size of the city. (Same
              function as show city button.)
  Close     - Closes the city information window


City data
  General        - Choosing one of these menu items is the same as setting
  Economy          the cycle gadget: the relevant information for that city
  Infrastructure   of the type described by the menu item will be displayed
  Tourism          (if available)
  History
  Others


Others
  Print function - This menu item calls up the print function window, which
                   allows the information in the window to be printed, or all
                   the information about the current city.
                   Usage information can be found at @{"Print function" link "Druckausgabe" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Druckausgabe" "Print function"
 11. @{u}Print function@{uu}

 GeoWorld makes it possible to print out the available data for the countries
and cities.

 You can select the "Print function" in the Others menu from the country and
city information windows. When selected, the "Print function" window appears
with the following contents (the title bar of the window will tell you if you
are printing information about countries or cities):

Only information - Prints out the contents of the current information window.
in @{u}W@{uu}indow          Therefore only the general, economy, political,
                   etc. is printed.

All available    - Prints out all the information for the country or city.
information

Change letters   - If this box is ticked, all umlauts and special characters
ä,ö,ü,... while    in the text to be printed will be removed or transformed
printing           into their correresponding equivalents:

                      ć, á, ŕ   etc. change to  a
                      ä, ö, ü   etc. change to  ae, oe, ue

                   With this function faulty printouts can be avoided for
                   some printers.

Destination      - This allows you to select whether to send the output to the
                   printer, a file or the standard Amiga clipboard. The name of
                   the file can be entered in the string gadget or chosen from
                   a file requester by clicking on the "<<" button (enabled
                   when outputting to file). If the destination is set to
                   "Clipboard", then you will be able to go into a word
                   processor which supports the standard Amiga clipboard and
                   paste the information into a document.
@endnode

@node "Menuefunktionen" "Menu functions"
 12. @{u}Menu functions@{uu}

This paragraph refers to all the menu functions, which you can call up
from the map window or from the control window. As you will ascertain
subsequently, the main menu contains some functions, which are achievable
only this way.


Project
  About - Brings up an information requester with following data:
              Program name + version.
              Copyrights + address of the authors.
              Statement about the (lawful) owner of the program, or "Not
              Registered", if it is a demo version, i.e. a program version
              without keyfile.
              After choosing the button "More", information about the
              currently loaded information in GeoWorld

  Quit  - Exit the program after a confirmation request.

Countries sorted by... / Cities sorted by...
  The countries or cities shown in the selection windows can be sorted on any
  of the fields within their structure. These groups of menu items allow you
  to select which field that the lists will be sorted on. Both menus also allow
  you to sort into ascending or descending order: for ascending make sure that
  the item is ticked and for descending that it is cleared.


Various things
Preferences  - Selecting this menu item will bring up the preferences window
               which contains the following adjustable GeoWorld settings:

  Always close windows
    If this box is ticked, all open selection and information windows are
    closed when you next click in the map window. (Makes it easier to see maps.)

  Immediately show the map
    If this box is ticked, selecting a country from the map, or a selection
    window, will immediately show the close-up map of the country.

  Show large cities immediately
    If this box is ticked, the major cities in a country will be drawn
    automatically when the close-up map of the country is shown.

  CycleToMenu Mode  (Only for owners of the CycleToMenu tool!)
    The text in the cycle gadgets (in country and city information windows)
    are returned to their previous state if the desired information was not
    available. Therefore, they always indicate what the information windows
    are currently displaying.

    However as said, this function is only applicable with an activated
    CycleToMenu (© by Federico Giannici), since with this, all items of the
    cyclegadget are displayed and can be selected from.

  Show title picture
    When ticked, the GeoWorld title page (full map of world) will be displayed
    when you run the program, otherwise it will jump straight to the world map,
    for country / continent selection purposes.

  Switch off sounds
    Switches off the (admittedly quite simple) wind and water noises on the
    map of the world.

  Expanded name search in Maxi-search
    Selecting this option makes GeoWorld search not only the short form of the
    country or city name (e.g. Spain), but also the full name (Kingdom of Spain)
    and also the name in the national language (Reino de Espana).

  Progress bar in Maxi-search
    If this item is selected, then a progress bar will be displayed after
    you click on the "Start search" button in the Maxi-search, allowing
    you to gauge the progress of the search.

  Flashing pointer at showing from
    When you are at the world map, or a continent map, choosing "Show country"
    in the country information window will flash an arrow near the selected
    country, if this option is selected. The same is true for cities with the
    cities option.

  Screenmode
    Allows the preferred screenmode to be set. Only screenmodes with at least
    640 x 400 pixels and at least 32 colours are valid.

  Font
    Allows the preferred font to be set. All windows are adjusted to use the
    new font and automatically adjust to the new font size.

    Exception: The city symbols in the maps are always labelled, using the
               included font GW2 (7 point) otherwise Topaz 8 is used. The font
               size is limited to 18 points; please try, if necessary, several
               fonts. There are some fonts at 15 or 16 point which are too
               broad for an optimal display, as some window borders may be
               over-run.

  Use
    GeoWorld "observes" the settings made for the current instance of the
    program.

  Save
    All settings are stored in the file "GeoWorld.prefs", and include:
      - the settings in the preferences window
      - the window positions of the selection and information windows
      - the settings in the print function window


Save         - Stores all current preferences in the file "GeoWorld.prefs",
Pereferences   without the need to first show the preferences window.

Quiz         - Calls up the quiz installed in GeoWorld - for further
               information see the chapter @{"Quiz" link "Quiz" 0}.

Organisations- When this menu option is chosen, a selection window will be
               displayed which contains all of the international organisations
               (e.g. NATO, UN) that are in GeoWorld. Clicking on one of the
               names will bring up an information window for that organisation,
               which shows the abbreviation, full name, name in German, the
               seat (where its headquarters are), year founded and number of
               members. This information window has two menu options of its
               own:
                 Members - Shows a selection window for the countries that are
                           members of this organisation.
                 Close   - Closes the information window.

Currency     - Two lists are displayed, both containing all the currencies in
Window         GeoWorld. To get information about a currency, select it from
               the "Source currency" list and click on the "Info" button, below
               the lists. The information window shows you the following
               information about the source currency:
                   Main unit (abbreviation of main unit)
                   Sub unit (abbreviation of sub unit)
                   Conversion between main unit and sub unit
                   International abbreviation
                For example, if the currency was British Pounds, then the
               information window would contain:
                   Main unit: British Pounds (Ł)
                    Sub unit: New Pence (p)
                  Conversion: 1 British Pounds (Ł) = 100 New Pence (p)
                Abbreviation: UKP

                If you want to convert between two currencies, select
               the currency you wish to convert from in the "Source currency"
               list, and the currency you wish to convert to in the
               "Destination currency" list. When you click on the "Convert"
               button, a requester will be displayed asking how much of the
               source currency you wish to convert. For example, if you wanted
               to find out how much UKŁ5 was in American Dollars, you would
               select British pounds in the source list, US Dollars in the
               destination list, click on convert and enter 5 for the value.

Save map     - With this menu item the shown map (including all drawn cities)
               can be stored as an Iff picture in an arbitrary file (selection
               via a requester). The further use of these maps is allowed,
               however it is exclusively for PRIVATE use!
@endnode

@node "Quiz" "Quiz"
 13. @{u}Quiz@{uu}

 Using the quiz it is possible for the user of GeoWorld to test their acquired
knowledge of the countries and cities of the world. Between 10 and 1000
multiple choice questions will be asked, with one answer always being correct.
As of version 1.08, the user can immortalise themselves in the highscore table,
in which there are twenty positions.

 During the quiz, select an answer using either the mouse or the cursor keys
(up and down), to highlight one of the answers. To complete the choice of
answer click on the "Confirm answer" button. GeoWorld will either tell you
"This answer was correct" or "This answer was incorrect, the correct answer is
...". The "Quiz end" button can be used at any time to exit the quiz.
@endnode

@node "Tastatursteuerung" "Keyboard control"
 14. @{u}Keyboard control@{uu}

 GeoWorld can almost be entirely controlled from the keyboard, for the choosing
of buttons, string gadgets, etc., using a set of keyboard shortcuts. These are
indicated by the underlined characters in the name if the gadgets.

Other keyboard controls:

° ">>" and "<<" are selected with the corresponding cursor keys (right and left
  respectively).
° "L", "R", "U" and "D" in the control window are selected with the respective
  cursor keys (left, right, up, down).
° The cyclegadget in the window @{"Maxi-Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0} can  be
  cycled with the spacebar.
° The three choices in the quiz can be selected by using the cursor keys
  (up and down) to move up and down the possible answers.
@endnode

@node "Hilfe" "On-line Help"
 15. @{u}On-line Help@{uu}

 On-line help is available in GeoWorld: if you press the "Help" key while one
of the GeoWorld windows is active, explanations and hints for that window will
appear. More exact information about the individual buttons can be displayed by
moving the mouse pointer over the gadget and then pressing the "Help" key.

Please note that the on-line help always refers to the current window.
@endnode

@node "Tutorial" "Tutorial"
 16. @{u}Tutorial - The GeoWorld workshop@{uu}

 This Workshop will show you more closely, using some examples, a further
understanding of how GeoWorld works. We have tried to make GeoWorld as user-
friendly as possible, and if you are familiar with the basics of the Amiga,
you should find the interface intuitive and may not need this chapter.


@{u}Example 1@{uu}

 For a geography test, we need all the available data for the country Angola.
We want this information once in printed form as well as once for further
use in word processing.

1.  First we open the country selection window by clicking on the "Country
   selection" button. When the window appears, select Angola from the list.
   This will bring up the country information window for Angola. Alternatively,
   as we knew the name of the country before we started, we could have typed
   "Angola" into the name gadget, in the control window, before clicking on the
   "Country selection" button; this would have made GeoWorld display the
   country information for Angola immediately, instead of the country selection
   list.
    The country information window should be showing the general information
   about Angola.

2.  Next, go to the "Others" menu (of the information window) and select the
   item "Print function". Alternatively use the keyboard shortcut "Right Amiga"
   + "D". Now the print function window should be showing in the middle of the
   screen.

3.  Switch on your printer, load paper into it and make it `online' - only if
   this is not already the case. To print out all the information about Angola,
   set the cycle gadget "Destination" to "Printer" and click on the button
   "All available information". You should soon be holding a copy of all of the
   information about Angola.

4.  Since we also require the information about Angola for further use (in word
   processing), set the "Destination" cycle gadget to "File". You will see that
   the string gadget for the filename and the "<<" button are now enabled.
   Click on the "<<" button to display the file requester - from here choose
   the directory and file that you wish to save the information into (e.g.
   "Work:Applications/WordProcessing/Angola") and click on the "OK" button.
   The full path and filename that you chose will be displayed in the string
   gadget - alternatively, you can type the full path and filename directly
   into this gadget. Again, click on the button "All available information",
   to save all the information about Angola to the file you selected.


@{u}Example 2@{uu}

 We would like to know, in which countries that have less than 1 million
inhabitants, English is spoken.

1.  As this is a search which requires more than entering the name of the
   country, we need to use the @{"Maxi-Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0} function, so click on the
   Maxi-Search button, or press the "m" key. The Maxi-Search window will now be
   displayed in the middle of the screen, with the title "Please enter the
   search terms:".

2.  Set the cycle gadget in the lower left corner to "Country selection", so
   that the Maxi-Search shows the search fields for countries, and thus
   searches on this data. Pressing the spacebar will also toggle the cycle
   gadget between "Country selection" and "City selection".

3.  To enter the search terms (as required from above), you continue as
   follows:
       Activate the field "Inhabitants" and enter "<1000000".
       Activate the field "Languages" and enter "*English*".

4.  Click on the button "Start search" to find all countries which have a
   population of less than 1 million and speak English. The Maxi-Search window
   will disappear and a country selection window will appear, which contains
   a list of all the countries which fulfill both search criteria.
    Selecting any of the countries, it is possible to see that these do, in
   fact, meet both search criteria.


@{u}Example 3@{uu}

 We would like to display the city "Abu Dhabi".

1. To call up the information window for the city "Abu Dhabi", we have
   again several possibilities:

   a. Click on the "City selection" button in the control window and pick the
      city from the alphabetically sorted list of all cities. (Please note that
      the field "Name" in the control window must be empty, otherwise the city
      selection may be biased from previous searches, i.e. "Angola" from
      earlier.)

   b. Enter into the "Name" field (in the control window) the search term
      "Abu Dhabi" (either in entirity or small amount of initial letters and *)
      and subsequently click on the "City Selection" button.

   c. Call up the @{"Maxi-Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0} window by clicking on the Maxi-Search button in
      the control window. Set the cycle gadget in this window to "City
      selection" and enter the name "Abu Dhabi" in the name field. You can then
      choose Abu Dhabi from the resulting city selection window.

2.  In the (now opened) city information window for Abu Dhabi, choose the
   button marked "Show city", either by using the mouse or the equivalent key.
   The map for the country that the city is in is loaded (United Arab Emirates)
   and the city Abu Dhabi is drawn at its correct geographical location.
@endnode

@node "TipsUndTricks" "Hints and tricks"
 17. @{u}Hints and tricks@{uu}

Search for Zip Codes with "*" in @{"Maxi-Search" link "MaxiSuche" 0}.

The search function for the zip codes is alphabetical, so use "*" in the search
terms. This makes it possible to search for all cities in the zip code areas
"01..." by entering "01*" in the search term.


Window activating by keyboard

 From the beginning of the development, there was a function which should have
only belonged to the development time, but which has subsequently been added to
the program as of version 1.0.

 All opened windows in GeoWorld can be activated by a keystroke, using the keys
0 to 9 on the numeric keypad, thus:

        0       -       Map window
        1       -       Country selection window
        2       -       Coutry information window
        3       -       City selection window
        4       -       City information window
        5       -       Control window
        7       -       Preferences window
        8       -       Maxi - search
@endnode

@node "Updates" "Updates, support and registration"
 18. @{u}Updates, support and registration@{uu}

 The information in GeoWorld will be expanded and updated constantly.
This means that perhaps obsolete information will be replaced and/or new
information will be added continuously.

 Likewise, current (or future) bugs will be eradicated. Please inform us if
such an error appears (with as detailed a description of the problem as
possible - your configuration, system patches/commodities, what the error is,
how it occurred, etc.).

 For your wishes, criticism, inspiration and similar we naturally always have
an open ear.


The updates will be freely available from the following sources:

 ° our homepage:  http://www.freiepresse.de/home/jubee/GeoWorld.html
 ° Aminet and Aminet-CDRom's in the directory "misc/edu"
 ° if possible CDRom's of AmigaPlus, AmigaMagazin among others


 Depending on the number of registrations for GeoWorld, and thus the perceived
need for such a geography program on the Amiga, we also have broader plans for
future developments:

 ° more detailed maps, if necessary also with different displays
   (political and nature maps)
 ° in connection with this, the expansion with further information like
   mountains, rivers, lakes, connections etc.
 ° Linking of landscape - and nature - photographs
 ° PowerPC version
 ° Realization of the wishes by registered users
 ° perhaps CDRom production

@{b}Registration:@{ub}

 Registration enables all funtions within GeoWorld, and allows you to sleep
with a clear conscience. When you register, you will receive a keyfile which
contains your name, address and registration number, enabling all functions.

You can receive your keyfile in one of two ways: by post or by email. If
recieving by email, you will be sent the 3 disks as DMS files with keyfile and
is cheaper. However, if you recieve by post, you will recieve the keyfile on a
set of disks which also contain the latest version of GeoWorld, and a printed
manual.

